For the Germans, the architects of victory were:
*   [Wilhelm I](/Wilhelm_I), King of Prussia and soon-to-be German Emperor.
*   [Otto von Bismarck](/Otto_von_Bismarck), the cunning Chancellor, pulling the strings with remarkable dexterity.
*   [Helmuth Moltke](/Helmuth_von_Moltke_the_Elder), the elder, the strategic genius of the Prussian General Staff.
